# Unified Canvas Architecture Plan

The plan outlines the transition from traditional web layout hierarchies (Headers, Footers, Public vs. Protected contexts) into a single, immersive 3D Canvas application experience with floating 2D UI tools.

## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> This is a significant architectural change that breaks away from conventional DOM-flow layouts. Routing structure will remain Next.js file-based, but visual rendering will rely primarily on a fixed viewport with absolute-positioned UI blocks over a WebGL Canvas. Please confirm this direction before execution.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Global Layout Restructuring
#### [MODIFY] [src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/layout.tsx)
- Remove the separate [(public)](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/canvas/CanvasEditor.tsx#78-182) and [(protected)](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/canvas/CanvasEditor.tsx#78-182) layout demarcations.
- Convert the main `body` element to act as a rigorous fixed container: `fixed inset-0 w-full h-full overflow-hidden`.
- Apply the dotted grid background pattern directly to the root body.
- Wrap all route `children` inside a new `<UnifiedLayout>` component.

### 2. The 3D Base Layer (Canvas)
#### [NEW] `src/components/canvas/Canvas.tsx`
- Create a generic base Canvas component inspired by [CanvasEditor.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/canvas/CanvasEditor.tsx).
- Include `<Canvas />` from `@react-three/fiber` configured with `alpha={true}` for a transparent background so the dotted CSS grid shows through.
- Implement basic `CameraControls`, lighting, and `Suspense` logic.
- Ensure z-index is managed explicitly so it sits behind the DOM UI layer.

### 3. The 2D UI Overlay Layer (Tools)
#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx`
- A strictly absolute-positioned container (`absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none z-50`) that houses all floating interface modules. 
- Elements inside will use `pointer-events-auto` to react to user input.

#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/tools/ToolsLogo.tsx`
- Render the `<Logo />` with the `post-it` variant, using `color="green"`.
- Hardcode dimensions to `48x48px`.
- Position: `fixed top-8 left-8`.

#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/tools/ToolsNavigator.tsx`
- Position: `fixed top-8 right-8`.
- Consolidate layout controls here:
  - Theme Selector (Dark/Light).
  - Locale Selector (IT/EN/ES).
  - Brand Color Selector ([SwitchColor](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/SwitchColor.tsx#14-55)).
  - User Authenticated Menu (combining login paths or the user avatar dropdown).

### 4. Cleanup
#### [DELETE] Legacy Layout Components
- Remove [PublicHeader.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/PublicHeader.tsx), `PublicFooter.tsx`, and traditional `LayoutProtected.tsx` structures wrapper layers.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1. Launch the app and verify that the layout spans the full viewport without native scrolling.
2. Confirm the 3D Canvas accepts basic mesh rendering.
3. Validate that the UI `ToolsLogo` and `ToolsNavigator` hover correctly over the Canvas and are interactive.
